Body: Description: FSAA Scan job is terminating mid job.  We see crash in the Event log and proc dump generates a file when left in the StealthAUDIT directory
What We've Learned Updated: R&D has been reproduced this in their development environment. They are actively looking into this. Nothing is required from the client's environment now.
Next Steps Updated: Waiting to hear back from R&D for next steps.

Key Indicator of error in event log: Windows Application Event Log | Event ID 0 - FSAAAppletServerCategory: Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.Applet.Server.ScanSession.ScanSession EventId: 0 SpanId: 2eabe52cbbba1046 TraceId: 5e8c89fbd0899d42217a3f4b913f5dfb ParentId: 0000000000000000 ConnectionId: REDACTED RequestId: REDACTED:00000002 RequestPath: /initialize Named pipe server timed out

Why the stacktrace relates to the issue is that SafeAccessTokenHandles are not being finalized, so when our code re-impersonates, there are none left. This could happen with other OS resources that have a limit however:   --- CODE ---System.Security.SecurityException atSystem.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity.SafeImpersonate(Microsoft.Win32.SafeHandles.SafeAccessTokenHandle,System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity, System.Threading.StackCrawlMarkByRef) atSystem.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity.Impersonate(System.Threading.StackCrawlMarkByRef) atSystem.Security.SecurityContext.SetSecurityContext(System.Security.SecurityContext,Reader, Boolean, System.Threading.StackCrawlMark ByRef) atSystem.Threading.ExecutionContext.SetExecutionContext(System.Threading.ExecutionContext,Boolean) atSystem.Threading.ExecutionContext.RunInternal(System.Threading.ExecutionContext,System.Threading.ContextCallback, System.Object, Boolean) atSystem.Threading.ExecutionContext.Run(System.Threading.ExecutionContext,System.Threading.ContextCallback, System.Object, Boolean) atSystem.Threading.ExecutionContext.Run(System.Threading.ExecutionContext,System.Threading.ContextCallback, System.Object) atSystem.Net.ContextAwareResult.Complete(IntPtr) atSystem.Net.LazyAsyncResult.ProtectedInvokeCallback(System.Object, IntPtr) atSystem.Net.Sockets.BaseOverlappedAsyncResult.CompletionPortCallback(UInt32,UInt32, System.Threading.NativeOverlapped*) atSystem.Threading._IOCompletionCallback.PerformIOCompletionCallback(UInt32,UInt32, System.Threading.NativeOverlapped*)--- CODE --- In the EventLogs, souce: .NET Runtime, Application: StealthAudit.EXE
